Patch Set 22:

> Patch Set 22:
> 
> Because we are calling write primitives multiple times consecutively for the same 'gss reply', I am afraid unbuffered could be counter-productive. Maybe line-buffered could be suitable, as long as there is no limit on the size of the 'line' (before it gets flushed).

unbuffered is not working indeed.
I mitigated the problem simply increasing the buffer size, using a 4KB buffer instead. Working so far...

        rc = setvbuf(f, buffer, _IOFBF, 4096);
        if (rc) {
                printerr(LL_ERR, "ERROR: %s: could not change buffering\n",
                        __func__);
                goto out_path;
        }
